{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":812,"text":"In the next ten minutes,\nwe will immerse ourselves"},{"time":3560,"text":"in an amazing and beautiful marine world"},{"time":6167,"text":"that's very often overlooked."},{"time":8605,"text":"I'd like to take you\non a journey into the sea,"},{"time":10892,"text":"looking at it from the perspective\nof its smallest inhabitants:"},{"time":14500,"text":"the microbes."},{"time":15892,"text":"My goal is that after this short journey,"},{"time":18316,"text":"you'll share my amazement\nat how deeply connected our lives are"},{"time":22373,"text":"to these microscopic creatures"},{"time":24199,"text":"and also perhaps my concern"},{"time":26396,"text":"that these relationships\nare often neglected"},{"time":29188,"text":"when it comes to making decisions\nand policies about our oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34595,"text":"When you look out on a clear blue ocean,"},{"time":37584,"text":"you're actually gazing at\na microbial soup full of vibrant life."},{"time":41634,"text":"What you see here\nare marine bacteria buzzing about"},{"time":45459,"text":"and exploring other members\nof the marine food web."},{"time":48097,"text":"To emphasize how small\nthis world really is,"},{"time":52465,"text":"I've added a white line\nto most of my slides"},{"time":56338,"text":"that shows you the thickness\nof a single strand of human hair --"},{"time":59732,"text":"very tiny."},{"time":60914,"text":"An average teaspoon of clean seawater\nhas five million bacteria"},{"time":65947,"text":"and 50 million viruses in it."},{"time":68030,"text":"If I were to scoop up\ntwo gallons of seawater,"},{"time":71316,"text":"there would be more bacteria\nin those two gallons"},{"time":73811,"text":"than there are people on this planet."},{"time":76709,"text":"Take just a moment and think about"},{"time":78963,"text":"how many gallons might make up an ocean."},{"time":81649,"text":"Or maybe I've already made\nyour stomach turn,"},{"time":83823,"text":"as you think of all of the seawater\nwe've each accidentally swallowed"},{"time":87147,"text":"over the years."},{"time":88397,"text":"But luckily, we rarely get sick\nfrom that seawater,"},{"time":91399,"text":"because most marine microbes\nare working for us,"},{"time":94369,"text":"not against us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95588,"text":"One of my favorite examples\nis that they provide"},{"time":98900,"text":"half of the oxygen we breathe."},{"time":101081,"text":"In middle school, we all learn\nto thank the trees."},{"time":103812,"text":"And admittedly, they may be\nmore huggable than the microbes."},{"time":107372,"text":"But it turns out\nthat land plants only create"},{"time":110368,"text":"a quarter of the oxygen we breathe."},{"time":112425,"text":"Another quarter comes\nfrom macroalgae like kelp"},{"time":115425,"text":"and a full 50% from the microbes."},{"time":118364,"text":"Take a deep breath in."},{"time":120745,"text":"Thank the trees."},{"time":122672,"text":"Take another deep breath in."},{"time":125093,"text":"Thank the macroalgae."},{"time":127275,"text":"Your next two breaths --\ntip your hats to the microbes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130841,"text":"This picture is of a bacterium"},{"time":132698,"text":"that happens to be the single most\nabundant photosynthesizer"},{"time":136902,"text":"on our planet."},{"time":138094,"text":"It's called, \"Prochlorococcus,\""},{"time":140348,"text":"and this is oceans' oxygen-producing\npowerhouse and, I might argue,"},{"time":145627,"text":"one of the most amazing discoveries\nof recent marine microbiology."},{"time":150069,"text":"We didn't know it existed until 1988."},{"time":152998,"text":"All of human history has depended\non this little microbe"},{"time":156209,"text":"for the oxygen they breathe every day,\nno matter where or when they lived."},{"time":161109,"text":"And we've only been aware\nof that relationship for a mere 24 years."},{"time":165289,"text":"I find that astounding."},{"time":167003,"text":"How many more critical\nrelationships are out there"},{"time":169591,"text":"that we have yet to discover?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":171099,"text":"I see our relationship with marine\nmicrobes as parallel in many ways"},{"time":175249,"text":"to the relationship we have\nwith microbes in our gut."},{"time":179008,"text":"We've all experienced the wrath\nof unhappy gut microbes"},{"time":182170,"text":"at one point or another,"},{"time":183517,"text":"perhaps food poisoning or tainted water."},{"time":186046,"text":"But we may be less aware of the connection\nwe have with marine microbes"},{"time":190264,"text":"and the physical discomforts we can feel\nwhen those communities change."},{"time":195474,"text":"As an extreme example: the disease\ncholera is caused by a bacterium"},{"time":199852,"text":"that thrives in the ocean."},{"time":201524,"text":"So while most marine microbes\nare indeed helping us,"},{"time":205227,"text":"there do remain plenty that are not."},{"time":207739,"text":"Our relationship with the ocean,\nmuch like our gut,"},{"time":210991,"text":"is dependent on the right\nbalance of microbes."},{"time":213948,"text":"The old phrase, \"You are what you eat\"\napplies to our ocean microbes as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218501,"text":"To give you a sense of what\nan overfed ocean may look like,"},{"time":222078,"text":"here are two examples\nof me sampling seawater."},{"time":224635,"text":"On your left, it's a clean coral reef,"},{"time":227760,"text":"and on your right is\na nearly dead coral reef"},{"time":230701,"text":"that has a very intense fish farming\noperation in the waters there."},{"time":234617,"text":"You'll notice I'm only smiling\nin one of these two pictures,"},{"time":238717,"text":"and in the other one my dive buddy\nhad to be a whole lot closer"},{"time":242490,"text":"to capture that image."},{"time":244266,"text":"So if we were to take a drop of seawater\nfrom each of these samples"},{"time":249139,"text":"and put it under the microscope,"},{"time":250883,"text":"this is what the bacteria and viral\ncommunities would look like."},{"time":254095,"text":"So again, clean reef on your left,\nfish farm reef on your right."},{"time":257827,"text":"As we all have had a feeling of discomfort"},{"time":261664,"text":"from imbalanced gut microbes,"},{"time":264174,"text":"a fish swimming through\na part of the ocean"},{"time":266408,"text":"that has been overfed in this way --"},{"time":268197,"text":"in this case, by intense aquaculture,\nbut it could be a sewage spill"},{"time":271412,"text":"or fertilizer runoff or any number\nof other sources --"},{"time":274647,"text":"that fish will feel\nthe physical discomforts"},{"time":276931,"text":"of the ocean microbes being out of whack."},{"time":279401,"text":"There may be less oxygen present,"},{"time":281515,"text":"there may be more pathogens there,"},{"time":283495,"text":"and there may be toxins\nproduced by some of these microbes."},{"time":287157,"text":"The bottom line is that\nfrom their tiny-scale existence,"},{"time":290712,"text":"these tiny microbes have\na very large-scale power"},{"time":293939,"text":"to control how our ocean smells,"},{"time":296005,"text":"how it tastes,"},{"time":297259,"text":"how it feels"},{"time":298475,"text":"and how it looks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301221,"text":"If you take one idea away\nfrom my talk today, let it be this:"},{"time":305883,"text":"we have an incredibly important\nrelationship with these marine microbes"},{"time":309946,"text":"that have very large-scale consequences,"},{"time":312466,"text":"and we're just barely\nbeginning to understand"},{"time":314837,"text":"what that relationship looks like"},{"time":316579,"text":"and how it may be changing."},{"time":318196,"text":"Just as a physician will have trouble\ncuring a disease of unknown cause,"},{"time":322697,"text":"we will have similar trouble\nrestoring ocean health"},{"time":325319,"text":"without understanding the microbes better."},{"time":327425,"text":"They are the invisible engineers\nthat control the chemistry of the ocean"},{"time":330933,"text":"and therefore, what creatures\ncan live there,"},{"time":333135,"text":"whether or not it's safe\nfor us to swim there"},{"time":335464,"text":"and all of the other\ncharacteristics we sense"},{"time":338057,"text":"with our eyes, noses and taste buds."},{"time":340256,"text":"And the more we pay attention"},{"time":341680,"text":"to these small but very numerous\nmembers of the ocean,"},{"time":344757,"text":"the more we're learning\nthey do indeed respond to human actions,"},{"time":348396,"text":"such as in this fish farm example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350511,"text":"Now, as the past few slides\nabout coral reefs may have suggested,"},{"time":353868,"text":"I do indeed spend much\nof my time as a researcher"},{"time":356502,"text":"thinking about human-microbe interactions,"},{"time":359065,"text":"specifically on coral reefs."},{"time":361366,"text":"It turns out,"},{"time":362546,"text":"we're not alone in having\nour own protective community of microbes."},{"time":365848,"text":"Corals, along with most other\norganisms on this planet,"},{"time":369502,"text":"have their own protective\ncommunities as well."},{"time":372227,"text":"However, rather than keeping theirs\non the inside as we do in our gut,"},{"time":376703,"text":"they keep theirs on the outside,\nto protect them from their surroundings"},{"time":380629,"text":"So what you're seeing here\nis a three-dimensional image"},{"time":383959,"text":"of a live spot on a living coral\nwith all of its living bacteria,"},{"time":388316,"text":"that I took with some\nexciting technology --"},{"time":390443,"text":"a high-speed laser-scanning\nconfocal microscope."},{"time":393933,"text":"All of the red circles\nare the symbiotic algae"},{"time":397042,"text":"that live inside the coral tissue,"},{"time":399029,"text":"turning sunlight and into sugars\nthey both can use,"},{"time":402707,"text":"and all of the little blue dots\nare the protective bacteria."},{"time":408130,"text":"So when I use image analysis software"},{"time":411296,"text":"to highlight the outer layer\nof the coral in white,"},{"time":414576,"text":"you can see that there are still\nsome tiny little blue dots"},{"time":417515,"text":"above that layer."},{"time":419095,"text":"And those bacteria are sitting\nin a mucus layer,"},{"time":422445,"text":"which is also part\nof the coral's protective layer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426113,"text":"From the bigger perspective,"},{"time":427473,"text":"I spend my time thinking\nabout these relationships,"},{"time":429952,"text":"because too many reefs are going\nfrom looking like the picture on your left"},{"time":433581,"text":"to the picture on your right."},{"time":435034,"text":"Believe it or not,"},{"time":436219,"text":"the picture on your right remains\na very popular tourist snorkeling spot"},{"time":439785,"text":"on the island of Maui,"},{"time":441016,"text":"even though it's lost most of its coral\ncover over the past decade or so."},{"time":444661,"text":"Corals are getting sick\nall around the globe at alarming rates,"},{"time":447719,"text":"and we really don't know how or why."},{"time":451008,"text":"I see the microbes on the coral reefs,\nboth the good ones and the bad ones,"},{"time":456181,"text":"trying to link their micro-scale\nbehaviors to this big picture"},{"time":460939,"text":"of: How do we help the reef\nthat looks like the right"},{"time":464655,"text":"back towards something\nthat looks more like the left?"},{"time":467294,"text":"Or: How do we stop\ncoral disease from spreading?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":469873,"text":"Just over a year ago,\nno one had ever seen a view like this."},{"time":473809,"text":"This video is a prime example\nof making the invisible visible."},{"time":479096,"text":"We're looking at a side view\nof the same coral as before,"},{"time":481970,"text":"where the protective layer\nmeets the seawater;"},{"time":484258,"text":"so, seawater on your right,"},{"time":485873,"text":"coral on your left."},{"time":487876,"text":"It's incredibly exciting to me\nthat we can finally see these bacteria"},{"time":491546,"text":"in real life, in real time,\nat their micro scale,"},{"time":495383,"text":"and learn how they interact\nwith the world around them."},{"time":498340,"text":"Ecologists all over the world\nare used to being able"},{"time":500865,"text":"to grab a pair of binoculars"},{"time":502233,"text":"and go out and observe\nwhat their study creatures do each day."},{"time":505595,"text":"But microbial ecologists\nhave desperately needed"},{"time":508429,"text":"breakthroughs in technology,"},{"time":510047,"text":"such as with this fast confocal,"},{"time":512044,"text":"to make similar observations."},{"time":515067,"text":"I work to find ways that cutting-edge\ntechnologies like this"},{"time":518787,"text":"can help make the unseen seeable,"},{"time":521928,"text":"to see marine bacteria in action\nand learn how they behave."},{"time":526023,"text":"In doing so, we can learn how they respond"},{"time":528900,"text":"to our actions and our behaviors\nand the environment around them"},{"time":532559,"text":"in ways that will help us\nbetter manage our oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535293,"text":"Another example of how I'm doing this\nis by using microfluidics"},{"time":543063,"text":"to study specifically how pathogens\nbehave in the ocean."},{"time":546971,"text":"The basic idea behind microfluidics"},{"time":548980,"text":"is that you can use\nnanofabrication techniques"},{"time":551701,"text":"to recreate or mimic\nthe conditions bacteria experience"},{"time":555814,"text":"at their own tiny scale in the ocean."},{"time":558446,"text":"What you see here is a microfluidic\nchamber on a microscope slide"},{"time":563458,"text":"with a microscope lens underneath it."},{"time":566093,"text":"We use high-speed video microscopy\nto record bacteria behavior."},{"time":570885,"text":"The colored tubing is where\nbacteria and seawater flow"},{"time":573634,"text":"in and out of the device."},{"time":575037,"text":"And it's using a device like this\nthat I recently discovered"},{"time":579017,"text":"that a known coral pathogen\nactually has the ability"},{"time":582086,"text":"to sniff around the seawater\nand hunt for corals."},{"time":586547,"text":"Here's the video of in action."},{"time":588648,"text":"You'll see all of the pathogens\nwhich are the tiny green dots on the left"},{"time":593427,"text":"start detecting the coral mucus I put\non the right side of the channel,"},{"time":597220,"text":"and they swim quickly\nover in that direction and stay there."},{"time":601667,"text":"Up until now, it was thought"},{"time":603547,"text":"that a pathogen would need some good luck\nto find its host in the ocean."},{"time":608235,"text":"But simply by watching\nand observing, we can learn"},{"time":611897,"text":"that these bacteria are very well adapted\nto seeking out their victims."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616078,"text":"These micro-channels are bringing\nus closer than ever before"},{"time":619564,"text":"to understanding how bacteria\nnavigate that big blue ocean."},{"time":623506,"text":"It turns out that this pathogen\ncan even detect the coral mucus"},{"time":629039,"text":"when I dilute it 20,000 fold."},{"time":632415,"text":"So these bacteria are very well adapted\nto hunting down these corals."},{"time":638533,"text":"I'm currently testing\ndifferent environmental conditions"},{"time":642377,"text":"to see what scenarios make\nthis pathogen more or less capable"},{"time":646534,"text":"of hunting corals."},{"time":647911,"text":"By learning more\nabout what triggers the hunt,"},{"time":650574,"text":"we should be able to find ways"},{"time":652225,"text":"to help slow down or prevent this disease."},{"time":655370,"text":"There's also some evidence"},{"time":657022,"text":"that the healthy microbes on the coral\ncan fight off the pathogen"},{"time":662023,"text":"if the conditions are right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664865,"text":"So, one final image of a coral\nand its healthy bacteria."},{"time":668526,"text":"I hope you've enjoyed this short journey\ninto our microbial oceans"},{"time":671852,"text":"and that the next time you\nlook out at the sea,"},{"time":674157,"text":"you'll take in a deep breath\nof fresh ocean air and wonder:"},{"time":677453,"text":"What else are all\nof the unseen microbes doing"},{"time":680224,"text":"to keep us and our oceans healthy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":682794,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}